<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h1>Tutorial 16. Finishing the Peplum.</h1>
<p><strong>I have nearly finished decorating the skirt: just one more gore and I can start decorating the peplum. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>Let me give you some handy tips on decorating the skirt. </strong></p>
<p><strong>If you are sewing a skirt with two layers of fabric, like I am, </strong>and using thin fabric for the face and thick fabric for the lining to prevent the skirt layers from getting distorted against each other, then I recommend you should pin all princess seams on the dress-form beforehand.</p>
<p><strong>In this case, there will be no distortion when you spread the skirt out for decoration. </strong></p>
<p>Such distortion of layers is noticeable on the mock-up, and it will be even more noticeable on the full-size skirt.</p>
<p><strong>And now let us move to the peplum. </strong></p>
<p><strong>I put together two layers of organza with a layer of mesh fabric between them and cut out the peplum piece using my fabric burning tool. </strong></p>
<p>It is really easy, and I expect it will work as well for the full-size skirt.</p>
<p>I make a row of stitches along the inner edge of the peplum so I can gather it.</p>
<p><strong>The peplum is reinforced very well. It has become quite stiff and I am happy with the result. </strong></p>
<p><strong>I put the peplum on the skirt. </strong></p>
<p>I mark the levels of skirt princess seams <strong>on the peplum to make sure it is positioned correctly. </strong>&nbsp;<strong>It is very important </strong>because these marks will allow me to align the folds of the peplum with the folds of the skirt after I gather it. The train area of the peplum will stay straight, i.e. I will not gather it.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>When decorating the peplum, I will step 2cm from the row of stitches to keep the edge soft enough </strong>so I can gather it later. I will finish decorating the peplum after gathering it.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I pin the peplum to the skirt aligning the marks with the princess seams. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I take the thread tail and start gathering the inner edge of the peplum to match the waist circumference of the skirt and then carefully distribute all gathers. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>All gathers of the peplum are now neatly distributed over the skirt. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I fold and pin down the train area. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Structured%20Designer%20Skirt/Transcripts/Tutorial%2016.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
